{
  "text": "Note that \u03b8 2 is a function of \u03b8 1 as well as \u03b8 B2 , i.e. the coupled motion [CITATION_1] in the wire transmission is observed in \u03b8 2 . Placing both brakes at the base has the advantage of reducing the mass of the moving part. Rotational motion of each brake is sensed by the optical encoder mounted on the brake axis. A brake can generate its braking torque only in the passive region in which \u03c4 \u00b7q 0 is satisfied, whereq and \u03c4 are the joint velocity and joint torque, respectively. Let J be the Jacobian matrix and J i be the ith column vector of",
  "citation_candidates": [
